pesticide.PPE:
- Chemically-resistant Tyvek suit and long pants
- Chemical-resistant gloves made of barrier laminate, nitrile rubber, neoprene rubber, or Viton (≥14 mil)
- Dust-mist filtering respirator (MSHA/NIOSH-approved) with N95 filters
- Protective eyewear
- Shoes plus socks

Safety_Information.general_Info: PRECAUTIONARY STATEMENTS Hazards to Humans and Domestic Animals CAUTION
Safety_Information.if_In_Eyes: Remove contact lenses, if present, then rinse eyes slowly and gently with water for 15-20 minutes, including under eyelids.
Safety_Information.physician_Note: HOT LINE NUMBER For medical emergencies call CHEMTREC at 1-800-888-8372.
Safety_Information.if_On_Skin: Take off contaminated clothing and wash skin thoroughly with plenty of soap and water for 15-20 minutes.
